eties; in this case Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot and Malvasia Nera. Aged predominantly in large oak casks, it offers charming notes of sweet garden herbs, wild cherry and cinnamon. A flinty edge counters the ripe easygoing core and powdery tannins are yielding. This will give plenty of pleasure in the near term. Drinking Window 2020 - 2025</p></div></div>]",https://www.wine.com/product/antinori-villa-antinori-chianti-classico-riserva-2016/540487,italy,red,tuscany
